28/05/2004
MAMAIA, Romania -- European Commission Vice President Loyola de Palacio commended the progress Romania has made towards meeting all requirements for EU membership, saying that even the toughest reforms have been implemented in time. 
She met with Prime Minister Adrian Nastase on Thursday (27 May), on the sidelines of the ongoing meeting of European heads of state in Mamaia. 
De Palacio also expressed optimism about Romania's prospects of closing all negotiation chapters by the end of this year. 
(Rompres, Nine O'Clock - 27/05/04)
